  <refnamediv>
    <refname>gqpe-tags</refname>
    <refpurpose>Edit and show the image tags</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>gqpe-tags</command>
      <arg choice="opt" rep="repeat">OPTION</arg>
      <arg choice="req" rep="repeat">FILENAME</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>

    <title>Description</title>

    <para><command>gqpe-tags</command> is a command line tool to edit and show
    the image tags of one or more files.</para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>

    <title>Options</title>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h</option></term>
        <term><option>--help</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show help options.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-t</option></term>
        <term><option>--title=TITLE</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the title.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-a</option></term>
        <term><option>--album=ALBUM</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the album.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-c</option></term>
        <term><option>--comment=COMMENT</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the comment.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-d</option></term>
        <term><option>--datetime=DATETIME</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the date and time.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-z</option></term>
        <term><option>--offset=OFFSET</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the timezone offset.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-o</option></term>
        <term><option>--orientation=ORIENTATION</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the orientation.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-y</option></term>
        <term><option>--latitude=LATITUDE</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the latitude.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-x</option></term>
        <term><option>--longitude=LONGITUDE</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Set the longitude.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-s</option></term>
        <term><option>--shift-time=HOURS</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Shift the time in this amount of hours. You cannot mix this
          option with any other except <option>--quiet</option>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-r</option></term>
        <term><option>--reset-time</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Reset the file timestamp to the photograph one. You cannot mix
          this option with any other except <option>--quiet</option>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-p</option></term>
        <term><option>--print=FORMAT</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Print the tags with format. You cannot mix this option with any
          other except <option>--quiet</option>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-m</option></term>
        <term><option>--missing-gps</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Only print the path of images without GPS data. You cannot mix this
          option with any other except <option>--quiet</option>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-q</option></term>
        <term><option>--quiet</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Be quiet.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

    <para>With no flags the tags are printed. An empty string as parameter
    removes an individual tag. You cannot mix <option>-s</option>,
    <option>-r</option>, <option>-pr</option>, or <option>-m</option> with other
    options.</para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>

    <title>Format flags</title>

    <para>The following flags can be used to format the output:</para>

    <table>
      <title>Format flags</title>

      <tgroup cols='2'>
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>Flag</entry>
            <entry>Meaning</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%p</literal></entry>
            <entry>The file path.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%P</literal></entry>
            <entry>The file directory name.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%b</literal></entry>
            <entry>The file basename.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%t</literal></entry>
            <entry>The title.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%a</literal></entry>
            <entry>The album.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%D</literal></entry>
            <entry>The description.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%d</literal></entry>
            <entry>The date and time.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%z</literal></entry>
            <entry>The timezone offset.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%o</literal></entry>
            <entry>The orientation.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%y</literal></entry>
            <entry>The latitude.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><literal>%x</literal></entry>
            <entry>The longitude.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>

    <para>
      Also, any standard C escape character can be used: <literal>\n</literal>
      for new line, <literal>\t</literal> for tab, etc.
    </para>

  </refsect1>

